# Documentation Structure

All project documentation lives in `docs/` with five subfolders. Every subfolder has its own `README.md` as an index.

```
docs/
├── README.md                      # Index: what each subfolder contains, links to everything
│
├── curriculum/                    # For fresh engineers: step-by-step learning path (concepts + code)
│   ├── README.md                  # Curriculum index: reading order, one-line description per lesson
│   ├── 01-project-overview.md      # (example) What the project does, high-level flow
│   ├── 02-...md                   # Numbered lessons: concept first, then where in code; detailed & clear
│   └── NN-topic-name.md           # One main idea per file; define terms; cross-link "Next"
│
├── quickstart/                    # For anyone: get running fast
│   ├── README.md                  # Subfolder index
│   ├── SETUP.md                   # Clone, install, .env config, run locally (commands only)
│   ├── DEPLOY.md                  # Deploy overview (options and links)
│   ├── DOCKER_SETUP.md            # Full Docker guide: build, run, compose, logs, registry
│   └── IMAGE_UPLOAD_GUIDE.md      # Upload guide: formats, UI, API curl, notebook, batch
│
├── architecture/                  # For developers: deep technical reference
│   ├── README.md                  # Subfolder index
│   ├── OVERVIEW.md                # System architecture + mermaid graph flow diagram
│   ├── GRAPH_NODES.md             # Every LangGraph node: purpose, inputs, outputs
│   ├── TAXONOMY.md                # Full tag enum reference (all 8 categories)
│   ├── DATABASE.md                # Supabase schema, tables, indexing, example queries
│   ├── API.md                     # FastAPI endpoints: routes, request/response examples
│   ├── FRONTEND.md                # Next.js components, UI structure, customization
│   └── PROMPTS.md                 # LLM prompt templates, tuning tips
│
├── reports/                       # For manager: summaries and status
│   ├── README.md                  # Subfolder index
│   ├── PROJECT_SUMMARY.md         # Executive summary: problem, solution, outcome
│   ├── FEATURES.md                # Feature checklist (done/in-progress/planned)
│   ├── DECISIONS.md               # Key technical decisions and rationale
│   └── PROGRESS.md                # Mermaid diagram of implementation status
│
├── errors/                        # Troubleshooting knowledge base
│   ├── README.md                  # Subfolder index
│   └── NNN-error-description.md   # Created as errors occur during development
│
└── plans/                         # Phase-by-phase setup guides
    ├── README.md                  # Subfolder index (links to all phase guides)
    ├── phase-0-setup.md           # Project skeleton setup
    ├── phase-1-setup.md           # Vision analysis + React UI
    ├── phase-2-setup.md           # Season tagger
    ├── phase-3-setup.md           # All 8 parallel taggers
    ├── phase-4-setup.md           # Validation & confidence
    ├── phase-5-setup.md           # Supabase integration
    └── phase-6-setup.md           # Production + Docker + polish
```

Additionally, `CHANGELOG.md` lives at the project root.

## Rules

- Maintain the curriculum under `docs/curriculum/` per the **curriculum-learning** rule: numbered lesson files, concept-first and code-second, detailed and clear for a fresh engineer.
- When adding a new node or modifying graph logic, update `architecture/GRAPH_NODES.md` and `architecture/OVERVIEW.md`.
- When changing the database schema, update `architecture/DATABASE.md`.
- When adding or modifying API endpoints, update `architecture/API.md`.
- When changing prompts, update `architecture/PROMPTS.md`.
- When adding new dependencies or setup steps, update `quickstart/SETUP.md`.
- When changing Docker config (Dockerfile, ports, env vars), update `quickstart/DOCKER_SETUP.md`.
- When changing image upload flow (formats, size limits, endpoints), update `quickstart/IMAGE_UPLOAD_GUIDE.md`.
- When a feature is completed, mark it done in `reports/FEATURES.md`.
- When a significant technical decision is made, document it in `reports/DECISIONS.md`.
- Use mermaid diagrams in architecture docs for flows and relationships.
- Keep quickstart docs command-focused with minimal explanation.
- Keep reports docs non-technical and concise for manager readability.
